<ref name=BECKY_rss>Becky! requires BkBlogReader or BkRSSviewer or B.F.R or BkRssReader plugin installed for handling RSS and ATOM.</ref>
<ref name=BECKY_frnews>Becky! requires FRNews or BkNews plugin installed for handling NNTP.</ref>
<!--
<ref name=EmacsLDAP> An Emacs module named EUDC extends [[Gnus]]/[[VM (View Mail)]] and [[BBDB]] to support LDAP.</ref>
-->
<ref name=KDENNTP>KDE supports Newsgroups (NNTP) by the use of [[KNode]]</ref>
<ref name=KDEFeeds>KDE supports feeds by the use of [[Akregator]]</ref>
<ref name=KDEiCal>KDE supports iCal by the use of [[KOrganizer]]</ref>
<ref name=NotesRSS>Studio Blog Reader is one RSS reader application for [[IBM Lotus Notes]]. [[IBM Lotus Notes]] version 8.x introduced a native RSS reader.</ref>
<ref name=OutlookFeeds>Support of feeds is available in [[Microsoft Office 2007#Microsoft Office Outlook|Microsoft Office Outlook 2007]]. Earlier versions require [http://www.paradisoft.com/rsspopper/rsspopper.asp RSSPopper] plug-in.</ref>
<ref name=OutlookiCal>[[ICalendar#Microsoft Outlook|Microsoft Outlook support of iCalendar]] varies by version.</ref>
<ref name=SelectiveDownload>''Selective Download filters'' can skip/delete messages on POP3 server based on header (sender, recipient, subject, etc) information, this doesn't require to retrieve the full message body from the server.</ref>
<ref name=MessageDispatcher>''Message Dispatcher'' allows the user to decide which messages should be retrieved, deleted or skipped based on the header information (sender, recipient, subject, etc) displayed to the user.</ref>
<ref name=MTB>iCalendar is supported with an extension.</ref>
<ref name=Claws>RSSyl plugin is required to read RSS and ATOM in Claws Mail.</ref>
<ref name=Claws2>vCalendar plugin is required to handle iCalendar in Claws Mail.</ref>
<ref name=BAT_mygate>The Bat! requires MyGate plugin installed for handling NNTP.</ref>
<ref name=BAT_rss2pop3>The Bat! versions prior to 6.3 required rss2mail or rss2pop3 plugin installed for handling RSS and ATOM. The Bat! versions 6.3 and later have built-in support for RSS.</ref>
<ref name=plugin>i.Scribe / InScribe requires a plugin to handle LDAP.</ref>
<ref name=pegasusaddins>Pegasus Mail can convert Newsgroup messages and/or RSS feeds to emails through the use of free add-ons.</ref>
<ref name=conePOP3>Cone has an option to either keep all POP3 mail on the server, or download all messages from the POP3 mailbox.</ref>
<!-- <ref name=MailiCal>With Mail version 4, in macOS 10.6 Snow Leopard. In previous versions, Mail only links it with iCal.</ref> -->
<ref name="Evolution-rss">The evolution-rss plugin (provided as a separate package by many distributions provides the RSS functionality in Evolution.</ref>
<ref name=SimpleMAPI>Mozilla Thunderbird only supports SimpleMAPI.{{citation needed|date=May 2011}}</ref>
}}

