{{Infobox software | title = Geekbench | name = Geekbench 4 | logo = | logo alt = | logo caption = | screenshot = <!-- Image name is enough --> | screenshot alt = | caption = | collapsible = <!-- Any text here will collapse the screenshot --> | developer = Primate Labs Inc. | discontinued = <!-- Set to yes if software is discontinued, otherwise omit --> | ver layout = <!-- simple (default) or stacked --> | latest release version = 4.2.2 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2018|02|15|df=yes/no}} | status = Active | programming language = [[C++]], [[C (programming language)|C]], [[Objective-C]], [[Python (programming language)|Python]], [[Ruby (programming language)|Ruby]] | operating system = [[macOS]], [[Windows]], [[Linux]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] | platform = [[x86-64]], ARM | language = English | language count = <!-- Number only --> | language footnote = | genre = Benchmark (computing) | license = | alexa = | website = {{URL|http://geekbench.com/}} | AsOf = }}
'''Geekbench''' is a cross-platform [[Central processing unit|processor]] [[Benchmark (computing)|benchmark]], with a scoring system that separates single-core and [[Multi-core processor|multi-core]] performance,<ref name="etn-multiprocessing" /><ref name="prakash-mohan-NIT" /> and workloads that simulate real-world scenarios. The current version, Geekbench 4, uses scores that are calculated against a baseline score of 4000, which represents the performance of an [[Intel Core i7]]-6600U @ 2.60&nbsp;GHz. The software benchmark is available for [[MacOS|macOS]], [[Windows]], [[Linux]], [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]]. Geekbench 4 also measures GPU performance in areas such as image processing and [[computer vision]].
[[Linus Torvalds]], who is the creator and principal developer of the Linux kernel, criticized Geekbench versions 3 and earlier for showing partiality for ARM64 devices and being a bad performance measure of [[x86]]-based systems. He called Geekbench as bad a benchmark as [[Dhrystone]], which he and others have ridiculed for years.<ref>{{cite web|title=Real World Technologies - Forums - Thread Charlie re Apple and ARM|url=http://www.realworldtech.com/forum/?threadid=136526&curpostid=136666|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170421100127/http://www.realworldtech.com/forum/?threadid=136526&curpostid=136666|archivedate=2017-04-21|df=}}</ref> When version 4.0 of Geekbench was released his comment was, "Looks much better."<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.realworldtech.com/forum/?threadid=159853&curpostid=159860|title=Real World Technologies - Forums - Thread: Geekbench 4|website=www.realworldtech.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-01-05}}</ref>
==References== {{Reflist|refs = <ref name="etn-multiprocessing">{{cite publication |url = http://etn.se/images/expert/FD-SOI-eQuad-white-paper.pdf |authors = Marco Cornero, Andreas Anyuru (ST-Ericsson) |title = Multiprocessing in Mobile Platforms: the Marketing and the Reality |year = 2013 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160813082140/http://etn.se/images/expert/FD-SOI-eQuad-white-paper.pdf |archivedate = 2016-08-13 |df = }}</ref>
<ref name="prakash-mohan-NIT">{{cite web |url = http://searchdl.org/public/book_series/AETS/3/85.pdf |title = Evaluating Performance of Virtual Machines on Hypervisor (Type-2) |author1 = Prakash P. |author2 = Biju R. Mohan |publisher = [[National Institute of Technology, Karnataka]], Department of Information Technology |date = 2013 |deadurl = no |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160818185607/http://searchdl.org/public/book_series/AETS/3/85.pdf |archivedate = 2016-08-18 |df = }}</ref> }}
