{{Infobox artwork | image_file = Nymph Central Figure forThe Three Nymphs.jpg | painting_alignment = Left side | image_size = 250px | title = Nymph (Central Figure for "The Three Graces") | alt = | other_language_1 = | other_title_1 = | other_language_2 = | other_title_2 = | artist = Aristide Maillol | year = | type = [[Bronze]] | height_metric = 154.6 | width_metric = 62.2 | length_metric = 47.6 | height_imperial = {{frac|60|7|8}} | width_imperial = {{frac|24|1|2}} | length_imperial = {{frac|18|3|4}} | metric_unit = cm | imperial_unit = in | city = [[Washington, D.C.]], [[United States]] | museum = [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]] | coordinates = | owner = [[Smithsonian Institution]] }} {{italic title|noerror|all=yes}} <!-- template after the infobox to prevent the display of error message --> '''''Nymph (Central Figure for "The Three Graces")''''' is a bronze sculpture, by [[Aristide Maillol]].<ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!373128~!0#focus "Nymph (Central Figure for "The Three Graces"), (sculpture)"]. ''SIRIS''</ref> It was modeled in 1930, and cast in 1953, it is at the [[Hirshhorn Museum and Sculpture Garden]].<ref>http://www.hirshhorn.org/visit/collection_object.asp?key=32&subkey=9776</ref>
